  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">GEOP GIW</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Christian Aid Ghana in partnership with the Ellembelle District Assembly, GRATIS Foundation, Ghanaian Institute of Welders (GIW), and United Civil Society for National Development (UCSOND) and in collaboration with the National Board for Small Scale Industries, the Accra Metropolitan Assembly, the Ayawaso East and Ablekuma South Sub- Metros and the District Citizen Monitoring Committees (DCMCs) of the two sub-metros seek to improve local economic development opportunities for young people. The overall objective of the 3-year project is to foster strong civil society and local authority partnerships to promote local job creation, revenue mobilisation and expansion of economic activities in an environmentally sustainable manner in the Ellembelle District, Western Region, Ayawaso East and Ablekuma South sub-metros in AMA by the end of 2019. The 3 results areas are as follows;
&#x2022;	Economic opportunities for young people in the informal sector enhanced through strengthened partnerships for provision of business services
&#x2022;	Women&#x2019;s groups in the informal sector strengthened, their business opportunities diversified and existing businesses thriving at community level</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will aim to promote local economic development of the beneficiaries across Western and Greater Accra Regions in Ghana. The project aims to identify and groom young people and women to gain employable skills or be self-employed. The target population will be trained on; improved apprenticeships, International Institute of Welders (IIW) accreditation schemes, appropriate technology training programs, aquaculture and fish processing, improved agricultural practices, customer service training etc. 
The action will also build the capacity of MMDAs and tax officials to collect taxes and identify innovative opportunities for IGF as well as ensuring that they account to the citizens through platforms like the budget hearings</narrative>
  </description>
